WEBVTT

00:01:29.909 --> 00:01:31.580
And he said, "You know, like,

00:01:31.580 --> 00:01:33.900
your motivational speaking.

00:01:33.900 --> 00:01:35.890
You know, when people in
wheelchairs come to school,

00:01:35.890 --> 00:01:40.813
they usually say, like, inspirational stuff?"

00:01:40.813 --> 00:01:42.259
(Laughter)

00:01:42.259 --> 00:01:46.557
"It's usually in the big hall."

00:01:46.557 --> 00:01:48.770
And that's when it dawned on me:

00:01:48.770 --> 00:01:52.041
This kid had only ever experienced disabled people

00:01:52.041 --> 00:01:55.699
as objects of inspiration.

00:01:55.699 --> 00:01:57.560
We are not, to this kid --

00:01:57.560 --> 00:01:58.861
and it's not his fault, I mean,

00:01:58.861 --> 00:02:00.672
that's true for many of us.